(638, 1, '2018-11-02 17:35:23', '2018-11-02 14:35:23', '<p><strong>Segment:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Security, Multimedia, Networking </p>\r\n<p><strong>Short description:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Secure audio processing &amp; management system. </p>\r\n<p><strong>Details:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Audio stream processing (RTSP, RTP, ICY, etc…)</li>\r\n	<li>Audio streams management (convert 3rd party streams to PCM; layer management)</li>\r\n	<li>Unit testing, test cases development</li>\r\n	<li>Inter-process communication (IPC) development</li>\r\n	<li>3rd party protocol processing (Pandora protocol)</li>\r\n	<li>Media utilities development (parsing playlists, metadata, additional info)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Technologies: </strong>C/C++11, Boost, CMake, SVN/Git, CUnit, CppUnit, Qt unit test, Google C++ Testing Framework, SQLite, OpenSSL, Networking, Embedded systems, Linux, Postresql, audio management</p>', 'Audio processing system', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '470-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-11-02 17:35:23', '2018-11-02 14:35:23', '', 470, 'http://demo.pinofran.com/demo/IT_blog/2018/11/02/470-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(639, 1, '2018-11-02 17:35:36', '2018-11-02 14:35:36', '<p><strong>Segment:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Security, Cryptography, Networking, Multimedia, Android </p>\r\n<p><strong>Short description:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Technology for protecting the premium content delivered through various network environments. Protection based on content encryption and trusted license management, which is responsible for content decryption. </p>\r\n<p><strong>Our responsibilities:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Project’s architecture development</li>\r\n	<li>Client-server SW development</li>\r\n	<li>Integration with open-source projects (Tizen OS, WebKit)</li>\r\n	<li>Integration with Android (Android MediaDrm plugin developed)</li>\r\n	<li>Developed multithreaded FastCGI module (linux daemon)</li>\r\n	<li>Vulnerabilities discovery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Technologies: </strong>C, C++11, MinGW, CMake, Google C++ Testing Framework, Git, SVN, SQLite, FCGI, nginx, Android NDK, Enterprise Architect</p>', 'DRM system (media content protection)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '472-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-11-02 17:35:36', '2018-11-02 14:35:36', '', 472, 'http://demo.pinofran.com/demo/IT_blog/2018/11/02/472-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(640, 1, '2018-11-02 17:36:04', '2018-11-02 14:36:04', '<p>Our team participate project in the HMI development for upcoming Mercedes-Benz model.</p>\r\n<p>Project mostly based on C++/Qt/QML, uses Linux environment. Between separated components networking is used. </p>\r\n<p><strong>Our responsibility on that project: </strong></p>\r\n<p>Features:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Architecture design of several components</li>\r\n	<li>UI implementation (QML):\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Implementation of base components, screens, menus, transitions, graphical effects</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>C++ plugins implementation:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Implementation of intermediate level between UI and backend</li>\r\n	<li>Networking communication with backend, data processing and preparation for visualization at UI side</li>\r\n	<li>Handling events coming from backend</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Implementation of mock backend, C#:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Implementation of mock server - hardware functions &amp; activity emulation (ignition, seats settings, engine status/settings, lights, sensors, etc…)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Automotive industry', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '474-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-11-02 17:36:04', '2018-11-02 14:36:04', '', 474, 'http://demo.pinofran.com/demo/IT_blog/2018/11/02/474-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(641, 1, '2018-11-02 17:36:51', '2018-11-02 14:36:51', '<p><strong>Segment:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Security, Analysis, Reverse engineering </p>\r\n<p><strong>Short description:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Linux daemon provides two functions:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Monitors applications activity, sends security reports to special server</li>\r\n	<li>Provides applications activity control, based on behavioral action patterns</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Our responsibility:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Parallelizing existing code</li>\r\n	<li>Integration with other projects</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Technologies: </strong>C++, CppUnit</p>', 'Anti-Malware Protection', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '476-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-11-02 17:36:51', '2018-11-02 14:36:51', '', 476, 'http://demo.pinofran.com/demo/IT_blog/2018/11/02/476-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(642, 1, '2018-11-02 17:37:05', '2018-11-02 14:37:05', '<p>This app provide a relationship of insurance employees with company clients. Thereby, support of clients occur the very fast, client gets a service without delays and in the small time. </p>\r\n<p><strong>Features:</strong> </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Each employee has a own login/password</li>\r\n	<li>Enhanced security using the role / group</li>\r\n	<li>Access to the contracts of clients based roles/group</li>\r\n	<li>The confirmation for the each contract</li>\r\n	<li>All user action writes to log file</li>\r\n	<li>And etc…</li>\r\n</ul>', 'App for insurance company', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '478-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-11-02 17:37:05', '2018-11-02 14:37:05', '', 478, 'http://demo.pinofran.com/demo/IT_blog/2018/11/02/478-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
