(911, 1, '2018-11-07 14:20:52', '2018-11-07 11:20:52', 'Develop of the ship device for search of oil spills.\r\n\r\n<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/2qXfZKu-r40" width="1143" height="611" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>\r\n\r\nThe radar and two radiometers that for obtaining data on the on board computer\r\nrunning ucLinux.\r\n\r\nUnder the operating system, mono was raised to run .NET WCF services that provide data access for user applications.\r\n\r\nThe device itself was designed to search for spills of oil on the sea surface,\r\nand was intended for fixed installation on ships in the Scandinavian countries.\r\n\r\nOur software, including the same data processing took into account the height of the wave,\r\nand by the angle of reflection I recognized the spill itself.\r\n\r\nMore info: <a href="http://ec.europa.eu/environment/life/project/Projects/index.cfm?fuseaction=search.dspPage&amp;n_proj_id=2684&amp;docType=pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PDF</a>\r\n\r\nThe present video: <a href="http://lifevideos.eu/videos/?id=LIFE02_ENV_DK_000151_02_EN_RISKM.mp4&amp;theme=RISKM" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Life Videos</a>', 'OSIS - Oil Spills Monitoring', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'osis-oil-spills-detections', '', '', '2018-11-07 15:54:41', '2018-11-07 12:54:41', '', 0, 'http://blog.softsln.net/?p=911', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(912, 1, '2018-11-06 11:35:33', '2018-11-06 08:35:33', '<p><strong>Segment:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Electronics, Embedded systems </p>\r\n<p><strong>Short description:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Development of software for the control stand - multichannel acquisition and processing of information from the temperature sensors, pressure, mass flow meters, and control of the frequency converter for the pressure pump motor power.</p>\r\n<p>The processes are controlled using Free RTOS </p>\r\n<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Remote control</li>\r\n	<li>Data analysis</li>\r\n	<li>Easy to extend platform with any kind of sensors</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Details:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Board layout designed</li>\r\n	<li>Microcontroller programming</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Technologies and libraries: </strong>Microprocessor - Processors EFM32LC256, EFM32HG210 and ADC ADS1248, C</p>', 'STAND FOR THE CERTIFICATION OF THERMAL ENERGY METERS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '314-autosave-v1', '', '', '2018-11-06 11:35:33', '2018-11-06 08:35:33', '', 314, 'http://blog.softsln.net/web-and-print-design/314-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(913, 1, '2018-11-06 11:43:53', '2018-11-06 08:43:53', '<p>Our team participate project in the HMI development for upcoming auto model.</p>\r\n<p>Project mostly based on C++/Qt/QML, uses Linux environment. Between separated components networking is used. </p>\r\n<p><strong>Our responsibility on that project: </strong></p>\r\n<p>Features:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Architecture design of several components</li>\r\n	<li>UI implementation (QML):\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Implementation of base components, screens, menus, transitions, graphical effects</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>C++ plugins implementation:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Implementation of intermediate level between UI and backend</li>\r\n	<li>Networking communication with backend, data processing and preparation for visualization at UI side</li>\r\n	<li>Handling events coming from backend</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Implementation of mock backend, C#:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Implementation of mock server - hardware functions &amp; activity emulation (ignition, seats settings, engine status/settings, lights, sensors, etc…)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Automotive industry', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '474-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-11-06 11:43:53', '2018-11-06 08:43:53', '', 474, 'http://blog.softsln.net/web-and-print-design/474-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
